main event: One witness observed multiple circular objects moving rapidly from East to West in Pequannock, New Jersey on May 9, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were evenly spaced and appeared about one second apart., The observed objects were described as huge and circular with no visible trail or sound., The duration of the observation was about 2 minutes., The report suggests a total of at least four objects were seen., The objects disappeared about 25 minutes after the last was observed.
sighted object: multiple circular objects in the sky
witness description: single witness who reported the sighting, with some debate among other witnesses regarding the nature of the objects
